---

# Internal Family Rules

### Approval Is Currency

Praise is rare.

Silence is often considered approval.

Disappointment is devastating.

### Emotions Are Private

Personal feelings should never interfere with family obligations.

### Reputation Is Collective

One person's mistake belongs to everyone.

### Duty Comes First

The family existed before you.

It will exist after you.

Your responsibility is to strengthen it.

---

# Story Function

The Liang Family represents duty, legacy, control, and sacrifice.

Their influence shapes nearly every major decision in Zhan's life.

The central conflict between Zhan and his family is not whether they love him.

It is whether love should ever be allowed to outweigh responsibility.
